**Segments**

- **Type:** The forklift truck market can be segmented based on types such as electric forklifts, diesel forklifts, and LPG/CNG forklifts. Electric forklifts are gaining popularity due to their eco-friendly nature and lower operating costs.

- **End-User:** The market can also be segmented based on end-users, including industries such as e-commerce, manufacturing, logistics, automotive, and food & beverages. Each sector has varying demand for forklift trucks depending on their specific needs.

- **Class:** Forklift trucks are classified into classes based on their lifting capacity and features. Classes range from Class I (electric motor rider trucks) to Class VII (rough-terrain forklift trucks), catering to different operational requirements.

